author: sam
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 21, 2019
review_content: My 4 and 6 year old love to play this game.  There was an older version of this game at a beach condo we rented for a week, and the whole family liked to play so we decided to buy it.  Just like the older version there are 72 thick cardboard characters, however this particular version my kids have figured out that if they look from the side of the card they can see the colors on the side that is facing down!!  Makes it very easy to find the matches!! So instead of using their memory as intended, they look for the color. So because of this I have knocked off a couple stars.
title: Kids love, but major design flaw

author: MOMaholic
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2018
review_content: I bought this for my 3 year old daughter who really likes puzzles and games.The pictures are clear and very pretty, and they are printed on thick boards - like puzzles.There are 2 different pairs of almost every Disney princess imaginable (excluding Elsa, Anna and Moana) and other minor characters from Disney movies.My daughter loves this game, and plays with it almost every night. We change the level of difficulty depending on her state (hahaha). For example, when she is tired or distracted, we just use 4 pairs of cards at a time, but then maybe 11 or more pairs when she is playing well. There are enough pairs of cards in the set that even older children should find the game challenging.All in all, a very satisfactory purchase!
title: Entertaining and educational

author: Lisa F
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 25, 2018
review_content: Great sturdy tiles!  My 3yr old niece loves playing games with my dad, and the matching game is their favorite. She always manages to school him in the game. And she adores the Disney characters on each tile as well.  Would definitely buy again.
title: Great game, great tile design.

author: A. Jones
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 5, 2018
review_content: Good game and the tiles are colorful & sturdy, but what was sent to me is not what is pictured. I'm guessing it's a new version. So instead of Tigger, Bambi, Thumper, etc. it has The Incredibles and Zootopia, etc.  I'm sending back because I wanted the classics that were depicted.
title: Nice but beware...

author: Soraya K
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2017
review_content: My 4yr old daughter loves this game. It has 74 pieces meaning 37matching pairs. The cards are thick enough to endure being handled by toddlers. Different & nice matching pictures on the cards.
title: Every little princess will love it!

author: yliebermann
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2018
review_content: My son is huge superhero fan but wasn't really into this at all. Part of the problem is that he only recognizes half of the characters. There are only 18 different superheroes and supervillains--for some reason they give you FOUR EACH as if they'd never played memory before. If you had to pick eighteen Marvel characters I'm pretty sure White Tiger and Nova aren't making your list, to the exclusion of, I dunno, even Ant Man, right? And forget about the X-men. They weren't allowed in this game.We spent more time punching out the cards than playing with them.
title: Disappointing

author: Frank Meeuwissen
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 10, 2018
review_content: My six year old niece loved this game. I will say that it can be a bit challenging for younger kids as there around 72 tiles (if I recall correctly). You can always just take out a few pairs to make it easier. Some of the tiles have the same princesses in different poses which can also add to the challenge, but all in all this is a well made and fun memory matching game.
title: Fun with lots of tiles

author: anon
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2014
review_content: Bought this for my classroom, and boy do my students love it. I work with multiple age ranges and skill levels, and memory is great for turn taking skills, game language, and of course memory. As a bonus the kids are so excited that its Marvel that is has been something that they ask to play daily. You get to identical sets in here. So if you do lose a favorite the bonus is you have another one.I would recommend breaking down the sets and putting them in bags. This way you can save a set for when the first one inevitably gets lost. Also there is no holder inside like a lot of memory games come with, so the bags help you stay organized.
title: and boy do my students love it. I work with multiple age ranges and ...

author: Via S.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 2, 2020
review_content: Great for Toy Story loving toddlers!3 things I may or may not change (see photo):1) I wish these had character names on them. I had to google half of them and finally had to ask a friend for “Combat Carl.”2) They come in sheets so you have to punch them out. This could be a pro if you have a kids who needs to be distracted for a few minutes. But definitely wasted time and packaging material for those who are environmentally conscious.3) If you look closely, you can see the background color of the pieces even when they’re face down. Maybe every piece should have the same border color?Hope you find this helpful!
title: Three things I might change

author: Larla P.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2020
review_content: We bought this to put in our four year old’s prize box that she picks things from when she does well in her homeschooling lessons. She was so excited to win it. After ordering, I worried a bit about it possible being a low quality item due to the super low price, mostly because I’ve bought cheap sets before that ended up being flimsy and having the thinness of a light cardstock paper. But this set was thick and cardboard-like just the way we prefer them. Blew my mind how high quality it was for such a low cost. Another good thing about it is there’s a huge variety in colors/pictures/themes on the cards which makes it easier and more fun to play. We’ve had sets (worst case being the Minnie Mouse set) where there’d be a bunch of pairs that were super close in appearance to one another, just with minor changes that are barely noticeable. The sets like that are so much harder for kids and way less fun. This set actually had a huge variety, none of the cards looked the same. There’s cards with single characters, character pairs, animals, symbols, snowflakes, child versions of the characters, etc in all different shades and colors and themes. Very easy for kids to play. Couldn’t be happier.
title: One of the best and most affordable Memory sets we’ve ever gotten. 5 stars.

author: FamilyofLove
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 20, 2020
review_content: There’s cards are very sturdy and the graphics in them are vivid. It came with way more cards than I thought it would! As you can see from my photo it’s a box full. It was too many cards for my 2 year old at once so I picked a few sets and let him just use those. It’s great for an older Toy Story fan because with all the cards comes a great challenge for any teen or adult.I’m super impressed by this set and I think it would make a great gift! My son loves it and so do I.I took the review picture against my skin so you can really get an idea of the length of the needles and what the roller looks like.Does it hurt? Absolutely. If this is your first time rolling, take a deep breath, and go for it. It’s super simple to use and super effective. We used it on my husband to help with his balding and we’ve noticed some of his hair coming back. Does it take work, time, and pain? Yes. Is it worth it, yes! It feels sort of like a tattoo and the aftermath feels like a skinned knee...but in your face. Don’t do it before you have to go somewhere!!!!I love the presentation, that it comes in a box, and that the handle is very comfortable to use. It’s a great item and you can’t beat the price. I highly recommend this item.If you found this review helpful, please click helpful to let me know! Thank you.
title: Looking for a great gift? Here it is!

author: Bobby D
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2019
review_content: I got this for my friends 4 year old daughter for her birthday.  She is a big fan of disney princesses, and board games, so this was a match made in heaven (no pun intended).  I was worried she might not grasp the concept of the game, but she picked it up right away, and was able to play and match and remember a lot.  I played with her a few rounds, and she caught on quickly and was quite good!  Great affordable gift that should provide a lot of entertainment.
title: Great gift for a little one

author: Kerri
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 31, 2019
review_content: Fun and cute game for the little ones. Love that they have all the characters from Toy Story 4 and come in different designs. Some are life like (just like they are in the movie) and some are more cartoonish (drawn and dont look computer animated)
title: Great value

author: seahorse
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2015
review_content: I was used to the better quality of the memory games of the 1980s.This game looked appealing, but it seems to be cheaply made. The individual "cards" or tiles are flimsy.The pictures on them, though of popular characters, are too much the same.I bought the game for my 4 year old grandson who was excited at first but by the time we finished punching out the cards he had lost interest.In addition, when he tried to open the box, not the simple kind with a lid but the kind that inexpensive puzzles come in, the box tore apart.His main concern after we gathered all the tiles was where we would put them.In future I will stick to the classic, traditional memory game.Truly a waste of money.
title: Marvel Matching Game

author: Amanda Powers
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2018
review_content: My Daughter is obsessed with this game (and always whoops everyone's butt!) It is a pretty large game! There are two sets for each picture. When we set it up it takes up half of our farmhouse table. The pictures are easy enough for kids to remember but there are so many pieces the memory aspect still applies. It is a great way to spend a rainy afternoon with the little one and it always blows me away that she seems to have a better memory than I do!
title: Get it!

author: Jared
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 14, 2019
review_content: My 3 year old absolutely LOVES this game! (Not to mention my 7 and 9 year olds will play with him and love it too!)The cards are sturdy. He has an old matching game with farm animals that are similar to poker card material. After a while they got all bent and it was easy to remember which cards were which based on the tattered backs. Not with this set so far!It also comes with 4 of each character and can be combined to make a really epic game of matching. Or you can split the deck for a shorter game. So worth every dime. This is my new go-to gift for kids 3 to 6.
title: Absolutely wonderful set! My kids love it!

author: Lily Solome
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2020
review_content: Got these for my toddler (18m at the time of purchase). We are slowly working on turning them upside-down to play memory, but she loves mixing them up and searching for the matches. She can identify all the characters by name (except the 3 fairies from Sleeping Beauty...I don't know them either).They come on sheets that you poke the cards out of. So we started poking them out, and found that she loves putting them back in and matching them that way.For an 18-24m old, there may be too many characters, but the boards solved that for us. We simply only pulled out matches for a single one, and let her put them in and poke them out. Then we would alternate characters. She loves it. And is getting better and better.
title: Lots of pieces, but amazing game

author: KellyC
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2017
review_content: comes with a lot of cards so I split it in 2 and sent part home with my daughter to have at their house. I wanted to find an easy way to teach my 2-yrs old granddaughter how to play games and take turns. It is fun for teaching and memorizing.
title: Lot of Different Cards and Characters

author: Maximum Verbosity
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2016
review_content: I bought this for a 4 year old which is the perfect age group for this game. They live sorting and matching at this age and the fact that it's Marvel Superheroes put him over the moon. He was one of the kids in my Christmas Adopt-A-Familybwith the St. Vincent de Paul Society, seeing him so excited & happy about such a simple gift made my entire Christmas season.
title: 4 year old +matching game +superheroes = win

author: Jeffrey
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 26, 2017
review_content: My two nephews are at the age where they're learning the things in their environment.  I sent this go-fish style of memory game in order to help with their colors, names, and number recognition skills.  My sister absolutely loves their nightly games of memory as the three of them try to memorize not only the character names, but also the tiny details in the brightly lit images.  The cards are small enough to fit in the child's hand, giving them a tact sensation which is attributed to memory.  Being a teacher I know the importance of memorization when it comes to school aged children.  Spelling tests are memory tests, multiplication tests are memory tests.  Get your child started at a young age memorizing objects, colors and sequences of things in order to give them a head start to their peers this summer before the new school year starts.
title: I See You See

author: Time2Buy
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2016
review_content: Purchased for our 3 year old great-nephew who is currently obsessed with superheroes.  Mommy loves the matching game for memory activity and toddler loves the Marvel theme.  Transferred to zippered plastic bag  and it is now the perfect game to travel with.  A great buy!
title: Nice Game for travel

author: Angie
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2014
review_content: I love this version of the matching game. The pictures are adorable. I mean who doesn't love Disney? There are 18 different images making 36 matching pairs (a total of 72 cards), so yes there are doubles. If you don't like having 4 of the same card in play then only use half of them. That would still be 36 cards in play, which is enough for the little ones. As for complaints of the pictures of bows, I don't see the problem, but take them out if you don't want to use them. When I was purchasing this game, I wished there were pictures of all the cards, so now that I own it I decided to post a picture for others to see. I think the picture sells itself and I think this product is well worth the money. Hope this review helps you :)
title: Great matching game for all ages...love it!

author: Rachel
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2020
review_content: You get what you pay for with this - it is a medium sized box with a few cardboard pictures inside. I like the variety of characters to match, but this just looks very cheaply made. Actually, you have to punch out the cardboard cards yourself - they come on sheets. That was probably the most fun my toddler had with this. I matched up all of the characters first so I could give my son a smaller amount to work with, and I came up short one piece. He hasn’t touched this since.
title: Cheap Looking Game

author: CL
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 27, 2020
review_content: This is much better than what I expected.  I purchased this in Feb 2020 and probably got a newer version,  unlike other reviews,  there is no repeat pieces.  True that they dont cover all popular avengers,  yet they include other characters that the kids get to learn something new too.Pros- very sturdy pieces- great value and giftable- no repeat pieces- combination of avengers,  villains and images- i like the set covers rare characters instead of the mainstream onesCons- can't find one yet ;)
title: Sturdy and not repeat pieces

author: Kendramatic
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 26, 2015
review_content: There are so many characters included in this game (some that I've never even heard of!). I bought this as a Christmas gift for my nephew. He just turned 4 and loves to play "the matching game" and with puzzles.It comes with 4 pieces of each character. When we play, we only use half of the pieces (2 of each character) and we keep the other set put away to use as backup pieces in case some get lost. The illustrations are (for the most part) well suited for children - less scary, less graphic, but there are still a few female characters in very revealing clothing and lots of cleavage to which he usually says, "Eww, what is she wearing?! You can have that one."The cards are of sturdy cardboard construction (perfect for preschoolers). It doesn't feel like they will fold or peel easily.
title: Lots of characters. Sturdy construction.

author: Flores
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2020
review_content: This is a great game to stimulate the kids and our brains. My son loves to play this game with us. It’s two and does really well. We started with a just a couple cards and have build up to playing with the whole deck.... with a 2 year old! lol it’s interesting to watch my son play. It’s also super fun to play with the grandparents. The cards are thick and the box is cane with was great in the sense it had a lot of eye catching characters. This would also make for a great Christmas present.
title: A must buy and a must gift

author: JG
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2020
review_content: I am rating this review not on the game itself (the games great, my son loves it) which is why I’m buying another for a gift. I ordered the exact same one that I did for my son but for the second time got a different marvel matching game. The characters are not the same as the one advertised in the listing. I mentioned this the first time I requested a return and had another replaced only to receive the same wrong item. Quality check or change the listing picture and description.
title: Wrong matching game sent twice-not as pictured

author: Shelly
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 29, 2020
review_content: Awesome little matching game, pretty straight forward. Pieces made out of thick cardboard, which is actually better then I thought it would be.
title: Kids love it.

author: Gary Christian
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2020
review_content: My 4 year old granddaughter loves match game, this one has way too many tiles , we ended up only doing half of what we got, I should of read it more clearly how many images.  Fun Game
title: Fun Game,

author: Mickey S
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2015
review_content: It's a matching game, what can I say?  Good quality cards and graphics, and way more pairs than you'll need for a basic game.  My major issue is for some reason there are 4 of most cards, I'm not sure if I got jipped or got more than I was supposed to, but it's worthless regardless as I just pull them out and set them aside when we play.  Also, something my 3 y.o. didn't really seem to have an issue with, is the similarity between characters, positions and color patterns got a little messy for me, with the background graphics as well.  We'll probably use the other matching games more frequently.
title: Decent game, not the best choice for just a matching game tho

author: LEP
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 17, 2019
review_content: Since when do matching games have sets of 4 to match? I've only heard of finding pairs of pictures when matching and staying there's 72 cards, there should be 36 unique pairs, right? But, in this game, there's 18 sets of 4 matching cards. So the product is pretty misleading. I guess the positive is that should you lose one or two cards you have replacements!
title: 18, not 36 pairs of cards

author: B.Adams
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 22, 2020
review_content: Bought this for my daughter's 4 year birthday gift. I have only used one of the 3 matching card sheets because there would be too many cards for her at this time.  She  loves them and I do too. Well made and pretty graphics.  I would definitely purchase these again for another child as a gift.  It was a good purchase- investment in my daughter's learning cognitive skills.
title: good investment for my 4 year old

author: Spazkatt
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 16, 2020
review_content: This was recommended by another mom and I am disappointed by it. The tiles are much smaller than expected about 2"×2" and made out of cardboard. Also there are no storage spaces in the box, since there are three different sets, it is extremely labor intensive to sort them if they get mixed up. I expect more from Disney and cannot recommend this game.
title: Disappointed in Disney

author: Sherry Walker Mitchell
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2020
review_content: I purchased this to play with my 3 year old grandson, Asher. We had lots of fun just going through the nice, thick, cardboard cards and making piles of the matches. It would be for a little bit older child to actually play the game, a 3 year old’s attention span is not that focused. It was fun, I’m happy I bought it.
title: Fun Toy For 3 year old grandson

author: Mandy R.
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 3, 2020
review_content: Purchased this for my son and he loves them. The images are great quality & vibrant. colors The card stock is thick and sturdy. My son is rough on these cards and they've yet to bend or break. The box the cards come in is way bigger than needed, but not a big deal. I would definitely consider buying another pattern/set from this seller in the future.
title: Great memory game for superhero lovers

author: godsnmortals
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2020
review_content: Big fan. The kiddo (4) LOVES these. We have a great time "playing" with these. Very nice colors/quality/thickness.I don't think the box needs to be as big as it is though. Lots of wasted space / takes up lots of storage space.Great set though. Would buy again / gift to my daughter's friends.
title: My kiddo loves them

author: Deb G
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 18, 2020
review_content: My granddaughter is 4, loves all things Frozen but... Although this game looks like something for her age the task of finding the differences in the tiles are too subtle and is not obvious enough for her but when she is age appropriate she won't like it because it will look to "babyish" for her.
title: Not sure the skill level necessary is appropriate for the the less mature looking game.

author: Nookentine
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2019
review_content: Bought this as a beginner game for my 4 yr old niece.  She absolutely loved it, "this is the funnest game ever," in her words!  She caught on quickly and didn't have a problem with using the full set of cards at the start!  The cards are sturdy and colorful, and we enjoyed hours of playing.  Would definitely recommend as a starter game for pre-school age children!
title: A great starter game - provides hours of fun and increasing  memory skills!

author: Miz
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2020
review_content: This is a wonderfully fun game for kids/families. I bought it as a Christmas gift for my 3 1/2 year old. He loves it, and we play it every day, without fail! The cards are heavy cardboard stock and vibrantly colored. I highly recommend it.
title: Great for kids and families

author: Eminem
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 2, 2019
review_content: These cards are very sturdy and colorful, too. I gave this game to my niece who loves these princesses so much that she's willing to sit still and play this game. She spilled juice on a couple of the cards and they still look as good as new.She plays it so often (and has gotten so good) that she won the other day. It was a rattling experience to lose to a four year old... but I guess that shows how much she likes this matching game.
title: Great Quality

author: Heather
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2020
review_content: Such a cute game, the pictures are super cute and perfect for a Winne the Pooh lover. The cards are a very thin cardboard so they will not last forever but at that price that is ok with us. Looking forward to playing with my 2 year old, just going to usd a few at a time and work up.
title: Winne the Pooh lover
verified: Style: Winnie the Pooh MatchingVerified Purchase

author: Ally
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2016
review_content: My daughter and I absolutely loved this game! The pieces are made of a durable cardboard. We played this as it is intended, a memory game, but, we decided to play "GO FISH" with the cards. Instead of saying "go fish", we would say "go princess". Lots of fun and great for all ages.
title: Fun with Princesses

author: Cece
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 14, 2020
review_content: Bought this for my 2yo who loves Disney characters. I’m glad I bought this on sale and not the MSRP. There are a lot of different characters but the cards are made from cardboard, so I don’t know how well they’ll hold up in the long run. Overall, my son like it mainly for the characters but I would pass on this.
title: Cute but would skip on this.

author: d.tramun
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on November 24, 2018
review_content: My 3 year old Grandson who loves all things Mickey and Minnie; just LOVES this game!! And he is pretty darn good at it!! He beats me almost every time! The game pieces are nice and sturdy- like thick cardboard puzzle pieces, with a wide assortment of Disney characters. Highly recommend this - it’s a great way to interact with your child or grandchild!
title: Very nicely made, good quality, and fun to play!

author: jdscham
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 13, 2019
review_content: Gave this as a gift to my 4 year old.  When we opened it, there was one tile missing!  Other than that, it was as expected and good quality.
title: Missing tile

author: Melanie Markunes
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2019
review_content: This is a super game to play with little ones. I play this game with a 4 year old and she loves it!!Cute pictures on the cards!! There are a lot of cards, so we use some and switch them out after several games!!
title: Matching Game

author: H
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 14, 2020
review_content: My son loves this game! It was a gift for his 3rd birthday.  I did subtract a star because the game arrived in an envelope style packaging which led to it arriving crushed (as seen in picture). This makes it less presentable as a gift and it is harder for my son to open and close it.
title: Great game but bad shipping packaging

author: Tiffany
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2020
review_content: Love love love. Got it for my 5 year old. He loves it and has a lot of fun with it. Takes it back and forth between home and grandmas house.It is a lot of pieces.... I don’t remember what the recommended age on it is. But you can always play with a little less pieces.
title: Love

author: withinthescars
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 9, 2015
review_content: Heavy duty. Son (22 month old) does not (cannot) bend them up!!! I've started playing with him using only 4 cards (2 pairs) until he gets the hang of it. He gets very excited to find matching ones. And it's nice having so many cards. If he loses one of two, that's ok.... there's plenty more!
title: And it's nice having so many cards

author: Alison
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2020
review_content: Gifted from my MIL as a Christmas gift for my three year old. He loves memory/ matching games. The designs are super cute and easy to distinguish. I rated 4/5 simply because there are a TON of matches- way too many for a three year old. We have split it in half to avoid hour long games (until he gets older).
title: Loved by my three year old

author: Land of Amy
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 28, 2019
review_content: my package came with 4 matching card per character instead of two so it makes it really confusing when playing the game for my 3yo.  maybe you are only meant to play with half the deck at a time but then why sell it with 2x the game pieces needed.  over all great fun for the kids but just hard to understand why the duplicate pieces for each character.
title: fun but weird

author: LongBeachgirl
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 22, 2018
review_content: The game will be great for my 3 yr old Grand-daughter.  I just wish it came with better instructions.  I think they are very weak.  I learned more about the game by reading the reviews.  I think it is great...to the point my Grandpa & Grandma made up there own rules to the game.
title: The game will be great for my 3 yr old Grand-daughter

author: Mimi of 6
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2020
review_content: Gave this  as a gift to a 4-year-old. We played it together and I think so many cards to choose from was overwhelming. I picked out just the cards with a large picture of a princess (about 22 cards) and we played with those. I think she liked that better, and she won. I think this game will grow with her.
title: Great Gift

author: Kindle Customer
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on July 10, 2020
review_content: Great game, good quality! We only play with about half of the characters to match with our two year old because it has A LOT of characters, which is a good thing for older kids or if you just want to switch character cards out once in awhile.
title: Buy!

author: lbeanburrito
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 12, 2020
review_content: I bought this for my 2 year old nephew to make cognitive learning a bit easier with disney characters. He loves seeing his favorite characters and matching them. There are so many cards and he even helped punch them out from the frame when we were starting to play.
title: Such a great memory game

author: Caveat
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on October 11, 2020
review_content: My three year old grandson loves this game! The cards are very thick, detailed, and has a large inventory of characters with name printed onto them. He loves this game! I highly recommend and will buy as gifts in the future.
title: Highly recommend

author: allison
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2020
review_content: I bought this as a Christmas gift for my 4 year old nephew that is obsessed with Spiderman and superheroes. He's also obsessed with learning. My sister said he will not stop.playing it. It's his new favorite game, and she appreciates that it wasn't another forgetful toy to add to the toy box of forgotten toys.
title: My 4 year old nephew LOVED it

author: GZ
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2020
review_content: My granddaughter absolutely LOVES Minnie Mouse, so when I found this game, I had to get it for her birthday.  When she opened the box, she wanted nothing to do with her other gifts…which means it was a great choice.

author: iiiireader
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on August 6, 2016
review_content: We're big Disney fans at my house so when I found these Disney Memory Cards, I bought them for play time with my grandchildren.  While my granddaughter is much too young to play, my grandson is having a lot of fun with these.  He is just getting introduced to a number of the classic characters whose pictures are on the cards and this helps him to remember their names as well as serving a great function in memory and visual recognition.I found the full set to be a little too much for him to deal with at his age, so I separated them into small sets that I keep in zip bags in the box.  He chooses which set to play with and we work those cards only.  As he gets older, I will combine the sets together until we are working the whole box.  Having several smaller sets to work with right now makes the value of the set even more appealing to me.He loves it when he matches the cards and we all applaud.  The cards themselves are nice and sturdy and the graphics are very well done.  I'm really pleased with this set and have purchased other sets in this line as well.
title: Fun memory card game for younger children

We are just introducing board games to her and this is a great way to teach the basics for setting up games and taking turns.  At first we just played by having her look for matches (with cards turned up). As she gained skills we started playing by the rules. You can use a few cards or many, games can last a couple minutes or longer. That versatility is great with little kids (and little attention spans.) Cards are good quality so we have enjoyed it for well over a year with no durability problems.

For example, there are four Spidermans, four Hulks, four Iron Mans, etc.I have Frozen matching game from the same company, and it has many of the characters from the movie duplicated. However, each pair of a character is unique from the other pairs of the same character. author: Table Top Games Dad
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on March 23, 2015
review_content: I played this game with my three year old daughter and it is amazing the kind of memory a three year old has! She surprised my Mom enough to post about it. The tricky part was keeping her attention when it was my turn so that she remembered what I had flipped over. There are so many characters in this game that you you have to have almost every Disney movie for your child to know every character. The game is simple, teaches memory skills, and is a great laugh when your child makes up names for characters. Mine started calling Dopey from Snow White, "Backwash".The only issue is in packaging and we had to find some rubber bands to group the tiles together as it takes a while to start because you have to collect and match all the tiles before setting up the game. You can get this type of game on your iPad or phone but this is a cheap and easy way to get the kid's eyes off a screen for a while. Plus it is easy to pack up and play anywhere. You can make it as easy or as hard as you want by controlling the number of matches you play at a time. My three year old can do 16 tiles well and begins to struggle when I increase it to more than 20. After about three rounds the attention span begins to waver.I recommend this game for it's high educational value, ease of use and adaptability to various skill levels.
title: Quick, educational and not a computer game

author: Jenny M. Rapson
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on April 13, 2014
review_content: The Wonder Forge provided me with this game for review, but all opinions are my own.This is your classic matching game with great Marvel character graphics just right for the preschool set. The images remind me of the Playskool Superheroes toys, which my 3-year-old loves. He has a speech language delay, but as I said, he loves these characters, so we are using this game to work on turn-taking as well as the concepts of "same" and "different" - and we are having a lot of fun doing it. There are TONS of cards, but before we play, I take out an appropriate number of matches for him, usually ten to twelve. So, it's very easy to customize the game according to your child's attention span. It's a lot of fun, if you have a tiny Marvel fan I am sure he or she would love it!
title: Simple, Fun Matching Game. Great for Young Marvel Fans.

The only negative is the edges are starting to come up a little just with use but it’s only minimal and we can still play with them so these were a great buy for the cost!
title: Great matching game

author: S. Brasher
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on May 19, 2014
review_content: Not quite sure how I feel about this product. I was excited when I found this game and I liked the idea of a generic Disney memory game vs. a specific character like Doc McStuffins or Jake and the Neverland Pirates. I have read reviews before on other matching games and the main complaint was that with specific themed games like Doc McStuffins, Princesses etc there were only so many characters and they were repeated on a lot of the cards (different poses, same princess) and that was confusing to children. When I came across this game I bought it due to the enormous number of Disney characters available, I figured no repeats and a lot of variety. Boy was I wrong. There are 18 different characters with each character's picture on 4 cards making 2 sets. I read some reviews which complained about no classic characters like Mickey, maybe I have a newer set but mine does contain a Mickey.The Characters are:Jiminy CricketLady and TrampNemoPoohPatch (101 Dalmatians)DumboFlounder (The Little Mermaid)Flower (Bambi)Marie (The Aristocrats)Baloo (The Jungle Book)BambiThe Cheshire Cat (Alice In Wonderland)Pumba and Timon (The Lion King)MickeyTiggerThumper (Bambi)Simba (The Lion King)Sebastian (The Little Mermaid)My daughter is 2 1/2 so this actually is probably a good thing that there is not a lot of variety as to make it too confusing. I know friends who have Memory games and they have to take out some of the cards because it is just too many for a toddler. This box is rated 3+ preschool so that is probably why there are duplicates and not a lot of variety. I just don't like the fact that I will possibly have to buy another set for when she gets older with more cards to match. My only other complaint is there is not a princess in the set. The makers of this game also went heavy on Bambi, with three characters represented from this film. Take one out and add a princess please. Finally, as other reviewers have said BUY THIS AT TARGET (or possibly Walmart). I paid less than 5.00 for this at Target and it is 12 on Amazon.
title: Torn about this product.

author: Olivia Stabler
date_of_review: Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2014
review_content: I got this for my 2 year old daughter who's obsessed with Disney Princesses and she really loves this game and we play it all the time. There are 4 of each card and some of the characters on the cards are Belle, Aurora, Rapunzel, Snow White, Ariel, Cinderella, Mrs. Potts, Sebastian, Flounder, and Pascal, so it has other characters from the movies in addition to just the princesses. The cards are thick and durable and all the photos on them are so bright and colorful.I love that it's educational in that it helps with critical thinking and memory. You can also use it to teach color recognition and use the cards to count. It's so refreshing to have a game that isn't inundated with noises and lights and that requires the child to concentrate to find the match. I also like that we can also practice taking turns with this game. Also, I can customize the game for her age level and decide how many matches I want to put out for her, like 6 pairs to find, so I can gradually make it more challenging for her. Highly recommended!
title: Fun, No Frills Thinking Game

author: FabricioFrias
date_of_review: Reviewed in Mexico on January 7, 2020
review_content: Se lo regalé a mi sobrina de 5 años y jugamos todos. Es bastante divertido y entretenido con los personajes de Disney requiere memoria y estrategia. Se puede jugar uno solo o entre más de dos. Aunque las tarjetas son pequeñas visualmente son bien diseñadas para viajar y que no necesiten mucho espacio. Son 72 tarjetas. Las tarjetas son duras y de gran calidad sin que se doblen como otras además se limpian fácil si se ensucian. Así que recomendado totalmente calidad y precio. Se pasan horas de mucha diversión el mejor regalo para niños que estimulen su memoria.
title: Para chicos y grandes

author: Daniela
date_of_review: Reviewed in Mexico on April 16, 2020
review_content: El precio excelente, me gusta que son bastantes pares, 36, y a mi hijo le fascinó, no deja de jugar, a diferencia de otros memoramas este es más divertido por los personajes y la cantidad de pares, las cartas son de cartón duro, excelente material.
title: Excelente y muy entretenido

author: Jose Antonio Rangel Casillas
date_of_review: Reviewed in Mexico on January 13, 2020
review_content: Las piezas son de cartón, pero resistentes y de buena calidad y buenos dibujos.Lo que no me esperaba es que todos los dibujos vinieran 4 veces y no sólo 2 como es en los juegos de memoria.Son 72 cartoncillos, pero sólo 18 figuras diferentes y en ningún lado lo especifica así.
title: Buen producto, aunque no es para hacer pares, sino cuadruples
